<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I would not recommend turning off attack<BR>every 10-15 seconds, you lose way to much<BR>damage doing that.  It is not really<BR>necessary either.  We do things similar<BR>to the above referenced post with some<BR>changes.  On the bubble diagram, we<BR>have the pallies and SK's stand on the <BR>sides of the mob, where it says no man's<BR>land at extreme mellee.  Only the MT<BR>and the rest of the Warriors in the order<BR>stand in front of the mob.  The rangers,<BR>rogues, and monks are to the rear.  Plate<BR>mellee on both sides,  The MT is in the<BR>mobs face and Waltzes the mob around<BR>in a classic BOX STEP WALTZ, by slowly<BR>circle straifing around the mob.  The<BR>pallies and SK'S help stear the mob from<BR>both sides and the rogues/rangers/monks<BR>are pushing the mob from the rear and<BR>the mob is surrounded and Waltzed in an<BR>imaginary box, to keep him centered.<P>We also sometimes, wall/rainbow pin against<BR>a wall, with MT switch sides from time to<BR>time if the mob slides one way too far.<P>The key to defensive tank switching <BR>sucessfully, is a nice little Defensive<BR>Macro our warriors use.  It activates<BR>defensive discipline and announces time<BR>left like so.  "Tanking with Defensive 3<BR>minutes left".  "Tanking with Def 2 minutes<BR>left", Then One minute left and finally<BR>"20 Seconds LEFT, TIME to switch TANKS NOW!"<BR>When the 20 second mark hits.  ALL MELLEE<BR>and Nukers stop completely, except for<BR>next MT, who starts climbing in the mobs<BR>face and TAUNTING, Kicking, Disarming<BR>and whatever else he can think of to grab<BR>agro.  The complete heal chain switches<BR>to the second tank right when they see the<BR>20 second MARK.  The first MT is still<BR>defensive but is cut loose from the CH chain<BR>while still alive, he dies within 5-10<BR>seconds of his 20 second message.  But by<BR>then the CH chain is going solid on MT 2<BR>and MT 2 gets agro because everyone else<BR>has stopped fighting for those 5-10 seconds<BR>and has been monitoring their agro closely<BR>from the 1 minute left message to be sure<BR>that MT # 2 is at top of list right after<BR>MT # 1.  If done perfectly, as soon as MT<BR># 1 dies, the mob should snap right onto<BR>MT # 2 like magic, and MT # 2 has a solid<BR>CH chain going on him because the CH chain<BR>switched to him while MT # 1 was still <BR>standing.  In practise, you sometimes also<BR>lose an overnuking caster or a rogue that<BR>missed an evade on the switch, but usually<BR>we pull it off without a hitch.  People<BR>just have to pay attention to that 20<BR>second left TANK SWITCH message and shed<BR>agro fast.  Our raid leader even gives<BR>a heads up message of "Get ready for switch"<BR>about 10-20 seconds beforehand so people<BR>can ease up on agro ahead of time.<P>We only do the defensive tank switching<BR>for Velketor and Vindicator now.  We just<BR>use two different timings and a single<BR>tank on most of the other mobs we kill and<BR>keep a single MT up by varying CH timings<BR>for defensive/non-defensive, slowed/unslowed.<BR>It is actually, faster and easier to just<BR>single tank and keep only one MT alive but<BR>tank switches are fun once you get the <BR>system down.<P>Bohric<BR>59th Cleric Innoruuk
</FONT>
