<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
One of the most important thing that the damage adders do is turn off their attack every so often.  It is exactly as Mybeasty has stated.<P>The problem is that the damage adders can inadvertently take too much agro and since we all know the agro is from a list which you raise in and lower down from you must be careful to ensure that you don't stay up on top too long.<P>The best guilds that take down the mobs know for certain that you must turn off your attack every so often.  Turn it off I'd say every 10 to 15 seconds for 5 seconds.<P>The main tank of course does not.  The main tank continues to taunt and keep agro up as much as possible.<P>I would not listen to a cleric that is trying to tell a group of melee how to manage agro.  I'd say rangers are about the best at managing agro and know more about how to drop down the hate list.  This is a given due to all the problems we had so many months ago.<P>It is important to remember that you must keep yourself not down at slot 2 on the agro list but down below that.  Slot 2 on the agro list must be maintained by the next tank that is going to take agro when either the first mt dies or his /disc defensive wears off.<P>--------------------<P>Metaphisto, 60 Ranger<BR>Rourke, 60 Cleric<BR>Thryll, 59 Necro<BR>Caution, 55 Wizard<BR>Loga, 55 Bard<BR>Rhose, 52 Warrior<BR>Tiggre, 52 Beastlord<BR>The Defiant<BR>Innoruuk
</FONT>
